    <section id="steps" class="container my-4">
        <h2 class="text-center">Recipe Steps for ca 50 cookies</h2>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 1: Ingredients</h5>
                <img src="1zutaten zu backen.jpg" alt="Ingredients to bake">
                <p>Gather all the Ingredients you will need. 
                    You need: 400 grams flour, 200 grams butter, 100 grams powdered sugar, 1 egg, 1 pinch of salt</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 2: Measure Flour</h5>
                <img src="2gewicht messen mehl.jpg" alt="Measure flour">
                <p>Carefully measure the flour to ensure accuracy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 3: Powder Sugar Size</h5>
                <img src="3pouderzucker verkleinern.jpg" alt="Refine powdered sugar">
                <p>If you add the powdered sugar, I would recommend sieving it to make sure it doesn't remain in too large chunks</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 4: Preview</h5>
                <img src="4puderzucker mehlen.jpg" alt="Flour sugar">
                <p>Here you can see how it should look like before blending.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 5: Tools for Mixing</h5>
                <img src="5werkzeug zu mixen$.jpg" alt="Tools to mix">
                <p>Prepare tools like mixers or bowls.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 6: Knead Dough</h5>
                <img src="6teig zusamengeknetet.jpg" alt="Knead dough together">
                <p>After blending it enough, knead the dough until it becomes smooth.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 7: Chill Dough</h5>
                <img src="7teig in kÃ¼hlschrank$.jpg" alt="Chill dough in fridge">
                <p>Place the dough in the fridge to cool. I would recommend leaving it there for about 30 minutes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 8: Roll Out Dough</h5>
                <img src="8teig ausrollen.jpg" alt="Roll out dough">
                <p>Roll out the dough with your rolling pin to your desired thickness.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 9: Cut Cookies</h5>
                <img src="9kekse ausstechen.jpg" alt="Cut cookies">
                <p>Now you can use the molds to press out your cookies</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 10: Place on Tray</h5>
                <img src="10ausgestochene kekse auf blech ungebacken.jpg" alt="Place cookies on tray">
                <p>Arrange the cookies on the baking tray.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 11: Preheat Oven</h5>
                <img src="11temp backofen.jpg" alt="Preheat oven">
                <p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees top bottom.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 recipe-step">
                <h5>Step 12: Bake Cookies</h5>
                <img src="12fertig kekse in backofen.jpg" alt="Finished cookies in oven">
                <p>Bake the cookies until golden brown and then your finished. Enjoy!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
